content.description: Some hard slapping gets you to better holds. Some holds look friable but feel surprisingly solid.
content.protection: pads, landing is two tiered so  spot is probably good.
content.location:
Start high reaching from the boulder in the landing: right hand on obvious right facing surprisingly-hard-to-rip-off ear, and left hand anywhere on the sloper.

As you walk into the hanging garden head straight across to the "Moon as my Witness" boulder and start navigating around the left side.  When you pass a big crumbly rock on your left skirt around the right side through a channel and you will arrive at the boulder.

Basically directly opposite Pangolin, behind the big crumbly rock.

content.description: Stand Start (left of large piece of rock that has fallen out) Powerful under cling moves and bad smearing feet lead you to a reasonable hold on the right side of the crack and a committing move to a jug further up the left side of the crack.
content.location: Number 2 on the area overview topo. From 'Final Round' follow the same Boulder down the hill.

content.description: Stand Start and climb up featured arête
content.location: Number 15 in the area overview topo

content.description: Sit Start at arête, climb up the short dike feature to a good hold. Make a big move up and left toward the lip, bring your feet up and begin the mantle process.
content.location: Number 20 on the area overview topo

content.description: Cool arete that is harder than it looks. Good edge on the arete make this more on a crimp climb than a true arete, but bad feet force you to use great body position and technique.
content.protection: There is a hole directly underneath the climb but a pad or two can make it flat.
content.location: From "I for an Eye" head directly west through a seemingly human made trail underneath the chossy arete overhang thing. Once under the arete if still looking west, this will be the left arete on the boulder on top of another boulder. Start on the lowest good edges, pretty far down in the crevice.

content.description: Very cool overhang arete feature, but TERRIBLE rock quality. Cool powerful undercling moves lead to a techy move or two to top out on the overhanging feature.
content.location: From "I for and Eye" look west. There is a small seemingly human made trail. From there you should already see a very chossy but kinda cool looking arete. Start underneath the arete on a large flake on the left wall and bust rightward through the prow. Use your feet on the left wall to bust some powerful move up and right too ultimately get you onto the prow itself.

content.description: Awesome channel feature through the face makes some awesome side pulls, which thin out for the top. Awkward landing makes this a little scary. Moving slightly right helps in ultimately moving up
content.location: From "I for and Eye", head directly west (through a seemingly human made trail) and go under a VERY chossy arete overhang thing. This is the face to your left right after going under the arete. Sit start in the lowest jugs

content.description: Follow the "wave breaking" lip. A hard move up and right from the slope leads to enjoyable easy climbing to the top.
content.protection: Pads can actually protect most of it but since you go over the tree that part isn't very protectable.
content.location: Start on the Slope jug of "Final Round" and just follow the lip. Ride that wave!

content.description:
One move wonder! Good-ish left hand pinch, right hand crimp and bad feet give you just enough to launch up to a jug.

Even tough it feels solid, I bet the "tongue" will one day break... but until then, enjoy!
content.protection: pads, landing is two tiered so spot is probably good.
content.location:
Start high reaching from the boulder in the landing: left hand on the obvious "tongue" right hand on an opposing crimp down and right.

As you walk into the hanging garden head straight across to the "Moon as my Witness" boulder and start navigating around the left side.  When you pass a big crumbly rock on your left skirt around the right side through a channel and you will arrive at the boulder.

Basically directly opposite Pangolin, behind the big crumbly rock

content.description: Stand on horn feature and climb up and left
content.location: Number 19 on area overview topo

content.description: Sit Start on right facing rail, make moves up and left toward a vertical seem/crack. With left hand in the seem/crack reach right hand for a small crimp and smear feet up onto the horizontal rail. Some balance moves get you to the top.
content.location: Number 11 on the area overview topo

content.description: Low start with left hand side pull and right hand in the horizontal seem, knobs for feet. Rough in texture but fun movement.
content.location: Number 8 on the area overview topo

content.description: Sit Start,  right hand on sloping arete and left hand down low in under clean crack. Moving left through a series of powerful hand bumps and a heel hook will get you to better holds, topping out on the short but fun climb.
content.location: Number 3 on the area overview topo. Just below/down hill from Trapped Under Ice.

content.description: A tough jump start leads to some tough slaps and feet moves to navigate the bulge.
content.protection: pad. Easiest downclimb is to reverse from the jugs and drop.
content.location: From King Nothing, head up and right toward "The Shortest Straw". After walking between the small channel between rocks this is the north facing "nose" on the big boulder. Start on a small right hand crimp on the right side of the bulge and jump to a good left hand meat hook.

content.description: Stand Start at the arête and climb straight up, some committing moves higher up will get you to the top.
content.location: Number 13 on the area overview topo

content.description:
Jump start to lowest scoop/pocket, work up and right through a series of pockets to some balance moves.

An extension to this problem is done by starting on the upper left shallow dish (Project 10 start) and then linking into Moon as My Witness.

A direct finish would exist but due to a tree branch that is holding up an oak tree I chose to exit right instead.
content.location: Number 9 on the area overview topo

content.description: Stand start at arête, left hand at bottom of  curved rail and right hand on crimp- both at head height. Bump the left hand higher up the rail then make a  momentum move going right hand up the sloping arête and left hand to the xeno knob! Make a right hand bump to the lip match and mantel.
content.location: Number 18 on the area overview topo

content.description: Stand Start at vertical seams, move up then right through a variety of holds.
content.location: Number 12 on the area overview topo

content.description: Stand Start, Match sloppy rail, using a crimp to gain another larger slopping ledge. Work the feature to mantle out.
content.location: Number 5 on the area overview topo. To the right of Dual Power.

content.description: Some very tricky and technical sequences get you though this cryptic and incredibly satisfying face! Just enough holds to be doable!
content.location:
First climb on the right when walking into the hanging gardens! Gorgeous face, with very few holds.

To the right of "Final Round"

content.description:
Tricky start leads to some easier climbing, exit left or right

there is a bee hive in the dead oak tree next to it, I haven't had a problem with them, but also noted is they go into their hive in the evening....
content.location: Number 6 on the area overview topo

content.description: Stand start, less than vertical face, left hand on the undercling/rail right hand on large knob. Make balance moves up and left, then once able to stand on large knob (right hand start hold) make a committing move out right to another large knob! Finish traversing right to the arête, then climb the arête to the top. Wildly Fun!
content.location: Number 14 on the area overview topo

content.description:
Sit Start this gently overhung face with left hand on arête just below the xeno mark and right hand down low on a small crimp. Smear feet and make a Big right hand move to a horizontal edge, left hand bumps up the arête to the jug. Turn the corner to one last trickyish move on a sloper which leads to a tall 5.7 slab finish.

Stand start, left hand arête below xeno mark and right hand on horizontal edge goes at V3/4

Stand Start at jug goes at V1/2
content.location: Number 1 on the area overview topo. The NW corner of the First large block on the right when you enter a the area. The arete will be sitting on another boulder.

content.description: High start on curved rail,  Match on the rail and using smear feet to gain a crimp, bring up a high foot and use a little balance and technique to work up the face.
content.location: Number 4 on the area overview topo.  If standing at Final Round you are standing on top of boulder and top-out of Dual Power.

content.description:
High start in scoop, make a hard mantle using a slim picking of feet and maybe a razor sharp crystally left hand crimp.

*Also the same start but connect into Moon as My Witness for a harder dynamic and thruchy extension.
content.location: Number 10 on the area overview topo

content.description: Stand Start at large void and climb up and left
content.location: Number 17 on area overview topo

content.description:
Stand Start at a jug, make a mantle move to small holds. A couple tricky moves lead you to better holds.

Descent - The downclimb is on the back of the boulder, just to the climber's left of Pangolin. Reverse-mantel down to the ledge or directly onto the flat rock below.

Alternatively, downclimb Out Cold
content.location: Number 7 on the area overview topo

content.description: Thin and sharp flake on the approach to the hanging garden area.
content.protection: Pad or some medium to fist sized cams

content.description: 5.7 crack on the approach to Hanging Garden area. Pretty fun little crack. Walk off the back
